A BISTRO owner who headbutted a customer after he complained about not getting a roll with his soup must pay his victim £1500. Bistro owner to pay £1500 over attack A BISTRO owner who headbutted a customer after he complained about not getting a roll with his soup must pay his victim £1500.Siroosh Bavarsad, 31, from Hyndland, was annoyed when he heard Graeme Noble complaining in the Clock Tower in Castle Street.At Glasgow Sheriff Court, he was ordered to do 150 hours unpaid work. 